      <h1 style="font-size:2.25rem;margin-top:1rem;margin-bottom:0.5rem">Facebook Ads for Home-Service Businesses: The 2026 Playbook</h1>
      <div style="color:#64748b;font-size:0.9rem">June 16, 2026 · 9 min read</div>
    </div>

    <div class="prose">
      <p>Home-service businesses — HVAC, roofing, landscaping, painting, pest control — have one of the highest ROIs on Facebook advertising of any industry. Yet most trade business owners either ignore Meta entirely or burn money on poorly targeted campaigns.</p>
      <p>Here's the 2026 playbook backed by data from 500+ home-service ad accounts.</p>

      <h2>Why Facebook Ads for Trades? The Numbers Don't Lie</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Homeowners spend 34 minutes/day on Facebook and 29 on Instagram</li>
        <li>55% of homeowners discovered their last service provider via social media</li>
        <li>Meta's lookalike audiences based on past customers outperform interest targeting by 3:1</li>
        <li>Video ads for home services have 2.4x higher conversion rates than static image ads</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Campaign Structure for Home-Service Businesses</h2>

      <h3>1. Lead Generation Campaign (Primary)</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Objective:</strong> Leads (use Meta's native lead forms for mobile)</li>
        <li><strong>Budget:</strong> $40–80/day per ad set</li>
        <li><strong>Audience:</strong> Homeowners 30–65 within 25 km service radius</li>
        <li><strong>Ad format:</strong> 15–30 second vertical video</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>2. Retargeting Campaign</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Objective:</strong> Conversions (send to website)</li>
        <li><strong>Audience:</strong> Website visitors (last 30 days), video viewers (50%+)</li>
        <li><strong>Budget:</strong> $15–25/day</li>
        <li><strong>Ad creative:</strong> Testimonial video + limited-time offer</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>3. Lookalike Campaign</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Source:</strong> Customer email list (100+ minimum)</li>
        <li><strong>LAL percentage:</strong> Start at 1%, scale to 3%</li>
        <li><strong>Budget:</strong> $30–50/day</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Creative That Works for Home-Service Ads</h2>
      <p>After analyzing thousands of winning Facebook ads for trades, these three formats consistently outperform:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>The "Pain Point Opener":</strong> Start with the problem — a sweaty homeowner looking at a broken AC, a wet basement, a leaky roof. Show pain first, then relief.</li>
        <li><strong>The "Day in the Life":</strong> Fast-paced montage of your team solving problems. Shows professionalism, builds trust, humanizes the business.</li>
        <li><strong>The "Neighbourhood Proof":</strong> "We just finished a roof replacement on Elm Street — here's the result." Hyper-local creative consistently has the lowest CPL.</li>
      </ul>

